ir voices and artworks as complex, serious and meaningful cultural contributions, and challenges their attested Otherness in favour for a more inclusive, all-encompassing understanding of art.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aArtzGreat Britain. 0aArtistszGreat Britain. 0aOutsider artzGreat Britain. 4aArt Brut. 4aArt History of the 21st Century. 4aCultural Anthropology. 4aCulture. 4aDisability. 4aEuropean Art. 4aExclusion. 4aFine Arts. 4aImage. 4aStigma. 7aART / European.2bisacsh  aArt Brut.  aArt History of the 21st Century.  aCultural Anthropology.  aCulture.  aDisability.  aEuropean Art.  aExclusion.  aFine Arts.  aImage.  aStigma.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2022z9783111025094oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022z978311076851040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839462508?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839462508423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839462508/original  a978-3-11-076700-1  DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076851-0  transcript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TGPb2022